    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-53 is a single chain synthetic human peptide, produced by fermentation in Trichoplusia ni. The starting gene is a synthesized copy of the human gene which codes for Insulin-Like Growth Factor Binding Protein 6 used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 240 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
